- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: With all control-module switches ON, measure the DC voltage between the two input terminals of the load module to confirm that about 12 V reaches the load. If 12 V is present but the lamp is off, then measure continuity across the series diode feeding the lamps and across each lamp (main and indicator) to check for an open diode or open lamps.
