description: With the new battery inserted, measure the voltage directly across the battery terminals and across the two outgoing PSU cables to verify that about 12 V is now present and correctly polarized at the PSU output., outcome='Battery terminals measure 12.0 V as expected. At the PSU output, the (+) cable is at about 12 V and the (−) cable is near 0 V relative to ground, indicating approximately 12 V present and correctly polarized at the PSU output.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module input and internal diode/lamp branch,
description: With all control-module switches ON, measure the DC voltage between the two input terminals of the load module to confirm that about 12 V reaches the load. If 12 V is present but the lamp is off, then measure continuity across the series diode feeding the lamps and across each lamp (main and indicator) to check for an open diode or open lamps., outcome='All control switches 1–8 are confirmed closed.  \nMeasured voltage at both load input cables (+) and (−) is ~0.0064 V, so about 12 V is not present at the load module.  \nContinuity for both the main load lamp (120 Ω) and the internal indicator lamp (500 Ω) is nominal; continuity of the load protection diode could not be tested due to missing resistance parameter.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=190.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> series chain between PSU output and control module 1, and sequentially between each adjacent pair of control modules,
description: With the new battery installed and all switches ON, sequentially measure the DC voltage between the two cables at the interface of each pair of modules: first directly at the PSU output, then at the input of Control Module 1, then at the output of Control Module 1 / input of Control Module 2, and so on up to the input of the load module. This will localize the segment where the 12 V disappears and reveal any miswired or open inter-module connection., outcome='The PSU Output Cable (+) is at about 12 V and the PSU Output Cable (−) is near 0 V, and this same 12 V / 0 V pattern is present at Control Input Cables (+/−) 1 and Control Output Cables (+/−) 1 and 2. Starting from Control Output Cables (+/−) 3 onward (including all subsequent control outputs and the load input cables), both the (+) and (−) cables measure at approximately 0.0064 V, indicating the 12 V disappears between Control Output Cable 2 and Control Output Cable 3. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED: all measured (+) and (−) labels are at consistent polarities with respect to ground.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=440.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
